'''Charles Tickner''' (born November 13, 1953 in [[Lafayette, CA]]) is an [[United States|American]] [[figure skating|figure skater]] who won the gold medal at the [[1978]] [[World Figure Skating Championships]], skating to music from [[Georges Bizet]]'s ''[[Carmen]]'' and [[Jules Massenet]]'s ''[[Le Cid (opera)]]'' for his long program. He also won the bronze medal at the [[Figure skating at the 1980 Winter Olympics|1980 Winter Olympics]] and the 1980 World Championships. He is married and has three sons, and he currently resides in the East Bay, California.
